The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Aug. 31 (PTI): Army chief General Deepak Kapoor, the senior-most armed forces chief, today took over as chairman of the Chiefs of Staff Committee.           eral Kapoor will look after the joint functioning of the army, navy and the air force. He took over from Admiral Sureesh Mehta who retired as the navy chief today. Vice-admiral Nirmal Kumar Verma has taken charge as the new navy chief.                   
	 New Delhi: The Supreme Court on Monday admitted a petition filed by Kerala CPM state secretary Pinarayi Vijayan challenging the sanction accorded by the governor to the CBI to prosecute him in the Lavalin scam. However, it refused to stay the proceedings initiated against him in an Ernakulam court in this connection.                   
	 Madikeri (PTI): A 13-year-old boy, who had allegedly stolen a revolver and Rs 5,000 from his employer, was arrested on Sunday from his home in Karnatakas Dakshina Kannada district. The boy had hidden the revolver in his pocket.                   
	 Tirupati (PTI): Prime Minister Manmohan Singh will visit the hill shrine of Lord Venkateswara at Tirumala on September 6. He will also lay the foundation stone for the nearby Tirupati International Airport and review important projects of the Andhra Pradesh government with ministers and officials.                                                                                                                           
